    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1911-12-20T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1911-12-20T00:00:00-05:00" n="1628"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1628">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 819.74/2.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                            <gloss type="to">Secretary of the Navy</gloss>
                    </hi>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1911-12-20">
                            <hi rend="italic">December 20, 1911</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have the honor to acknowledge the receipt of
                    your letter of the 11th instant in which you request such information as may be
                    available concerning any wireless telegraph installations existing or proposed
                    on the Isthmus of Panama.</p>
                <p>In reply I have the honor to say that an appropriate instruction, based on your
                    letter, has been sent to the American Minister at Panama City, and that, when a
                    reply shall have been received, the Department will be glad to communicate
                    further with you on the subject.</p>
                <p>I have [etc.]</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">P. C. Knox.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
